## 9. Key Decisions & Notes

1. **Lovable-generated** — The frontend was scaffolded via [Lovable](https://lovable.dev), a no-code builder. The output is clean and production-quality.

2. **Design language** — Editorial/journal-inspired dark theme with monospace accents, green/amber/blue/purple color palette, serif italic headlines, Framer Motion animations.

3. **No backend exists** — All data is hardcoded in [mockAgents.ts](file:///c:/Users/vg890/OneDrive/Desktop/agentid-kya-solana/exactly-as-seen/src/data/mockAgents.ts). The frontend is a pure static SPA.

4. **Wallet is simulated** — [useWallet.tsx](file:///c:/Users/vg890/OneDrive/Desktop/agentid-kya-solana/exactly-as-seen/src/hooks/useWallet.tsx) uses `setTimeout` to fake connection. Real Phantom/Solflare integration needed.

5. **Landing page roadmap is aspirational** — W1–W2 shown as "Done" in the UI, but no actual smart contracts exist yet.

6. **TypeScript types are well-defined** — [Agent](file:///c:/Users/vg890/OneDrive/Desktop/agentid-kya-solana/exactly-as-seen/src/data/mockAgents.ts#19-45), [AgentCapabilities](file:///c:/Users/vg890/OneDrive/Desktop/agentid-kya-solana/exactly-as-seen/src/data/mockAgents.ts#1-8), [AgentActivity](file:///c:/Users/vg890/OneDrive/Desktop/agentid-kya-solana/exactly-as-seen/src/data/mockAgents.ts#9-18) interfaces are comprehensive and match the Rust struct design from the idea doc. This makes frontend→backend wiring straightforward.

